{"id": 6404, "title": "Ticket #6404: Add support for MUNGE authentication", "description": "<blockquote>\nKevin Fox has implemented a first pass at supporting MUNGE for authentication.  This came to us via github pull request <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=12\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('12'); return false;\" title=\"condor_status always prints a tailing \\n to stdout\">#12</a></span>.\n\n<p>I have created the V8_7-MUNGE-branch to import and tidy up this contribution.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Sep-13 19:12:53 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nWhoever ends up reviewing this needs only to look at <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1be4a28ff5865ee00f657c08b7fbf4d30b259373\">[52346]</a></span> which is the squash merge into master.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-25 16:44:05 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong>\n\n<p>My only comment is that 24 bytes seems pretty small for an encryption key. But that's the same size we use for the session key, so it's no worse than the rest of our security stuff.\n\n</p><p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-26 15:15:07 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nIt's not obvious because of the squash merge, but MUNGE was added to the manual as part of the initial pull request.\n\n<p>I just added the version history.</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-26 15:14</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d7af95aa0cfd8d6a9d2be1d4990d38805762afd0\">[52673]</a></span>: Add version history for MUNGE support, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" hre